Whats New:

- Many Bug Fixes. You can now complete the game.
- Prisma music now loops during gameplay.
- External MIDI support (using the CAMD Library)

Overview:

Heretic is a dark fantasy first-person shooter video game released in 1994.
It was developed by Raven Software, published by id Software, 
and distributed by GT Interactive.

Chocolate Heretic is a port of the Heretic source code to the Chocolate
Doom codebase. The aim is to develop a Heretic source port that 
includes the features of Chocolate Doom.

This port was made possible by using the Heretic Branch of Chocolate-Doom 
Version 1.6


Minimum Requirements:

- Amiga 1200 (AGA) 
- OS3.1
- 68040/40mhz CPU (note the game will run on an 020/030 
at low framerates)
- At least 16Meg of FAST memory
- 60Meg HDD space


Recommended Requirements for Optimal Performance:

- Amiga A1200/A4000 with fast HDD transfer rates
- OS3.9 with Boing Bag 2 or higher installed
- 68060/50Mhz or higher
- 32Meg FAST Memory or higher
- Prisma Megamix music card

OR

- Amiga 500 or Amiga 600 with a Vampire 2 V500/V600 installed
- MIDI interface with a Roland SC-55 or MT-32

Usage:

1) You will need a copy of the commerical game. Place the 
following files in your Heretic folder :
    HERETIC.WAD
     
2) Double click on the Heretic icon and enjoy the game.



You can also run the game via command line by calling 'heretic' from the CLI - for example:

    heretic -aga


Other command line flags:

-cgx or -vampire2 will switch to RTG mode.
-aga for AGA mode.
-prisma for Prisma Megamix Music support
-camd for External MIDI support via CAMD.
-mmu will enable the MMU if you have a 68040 or higher CPU.
-ntsc will switch to a NTSC monitor ID (the default is PAL)
-nosound will start the game without sfx


Prisma Megamix Support:

You will need a Prisma Megamix card installed with 
the driver and the MHI library available 
in LIBS:MHI\mhiprisma.library

Heretic OGGs are available for download 
at http://sc55.duke4.net

The following filenames are required for 
uninterupted playback:
    mus_cptd.ogg
    mus_e1m1.ogg
    mus_e1m2.ogg
    mus_e1m3.ogg
    mus_e1m4.ogg
    mus_e1m5.ogg
    mus_e1m6.ogg
    mus_e1m7.ogg
    mus_e1m8.ogg
    mus_e1m9.ogg
    mus_e2m1.ogg
    mus_e2m2.ogg
    mus_e2m3.ogg
    mus_e2m4.ogg
    mus_e2m5.ogg
    mus_e2m6.ogg
    mus_e2m7.ogg
    mus_e2m8.ogg
    mus_e2m9.ogg
    mus_e3m2.ogg
    mus_e3m3.ogg
    mus_intr.ogg
    mus_titl.ogg

Install these OGG files in the Music subfolder and either select 
-prisma from command line or enable PRISMA from ToolTypes.

Prisma support might be buggy. Please let me know of any issues 
you may find!


